From 23a26d6ebed7ea58cb76c73f5f4fc8d7ea3d960c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Justin Le <justin@jle.im>
Date: Tue, 27 Nov 2018 17:53:06 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] fix all tests (NEIntMap.updateLookupWithKey return value)

Hand-crafted slice of upstream commit 23a26d6 against modern HEAD.

The buggy `updateLookupWithKey` returned `f k0 v` in the EQ branch,
which is the *post-update* value (`Just newValue` when the function
returns `Just`, or `Nothing` if it deletes). The corrected behaviour
matches `Data.Map`'s `updateLookupWithKey` semantic: always return
`Just v` — the *original* value at the key — regardless of whether
the function chose to update or delete the entry.
---
 src/Data/IntMap/NonEmpty.hs | 5 ++---
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/Data/IntMap/NonEmpty.hs b/src/Data/IntMap/NonEmpty.hs
index aaaaaaa..bbbbbbb 100644
--- a/src/Data/IntMap/NonEmpty.hs
+++ b/src/Data/IntMap/NonEmpty.hs
@@ -678,5 +678,7 @@
 updateLookupWithKey f k n@(NEIntMap k0 v m) = case compare k k0 of
   LT -> (Nothing, toMap n)
-  EQ -> (f k0 v, maybe m (flip (insertMinMap k0) m) . f k0 $ v)
+  EQ ->
+    let u = f k0 v
+     in (Just v, maybe m (flip (insertMinMap k0) m) u)
   GT -> fmap (insertMinMap k0 v) . M.updateLookupWithKey f k $ m
 {-# INLINE updateLookupWithKey #-}

